    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe fact that incsearch allows ctrl-g and ctrl-t to cycle through different instances of the matched string before accepting the complete motion is awesome, particularly when used in operator-pending mode.  Say we have the following line and our cursor is at the beginning in normal mode:\r\n`blah blah blah`\r\nWe can use `c/blah<ctrl-g><ctrl-g><enter>` to change everything up to the third \"blah\" (exclusive).  But what if I wanted to include the third \"blah\" in the change?  It seems like I should be able to make use of the {offset} (:help /) to do `c/blah/e<ctrl-g><ctrl-g><enter>` ; however ctrl-g and ctrl-t do nothing as soon as you add the second slash to specify the offset.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nDesired behavior would be for ctrl-g and ctrl-t to still cycle through potential matches and once enter is pressed, any {offset} specified would be respected.  In the example above, our change would include the third \"blah\" (we would be in insert mode with nothing on the current line).",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I made a pr for this. Namely, it fixes `c_CTRL-G` / `c_CTRL-T` stopping cycling once an `'incsearch'` command includes an offset like `/blah/e` (as mentioned above). With the patch, commands such as `/blah/e<C-g><CR>` and `/blah/e<C-g><C-g><CR>` keep selecting the second and third `blah`, and `<CR>` still applies `/e` through the existing search path.\n\nHowever, one thing I was unsure about is the live `incsearch` preview. For example, consider `/blah/+1` on:\n\n```text\nbefore\nblah\nafter\n```\n\nShould the live preview highlight `blah` because that is the regex match being selected, or should it move the preview to after, because that is the final offset-adjusted destination?\n\nI think that the live preview should continue to follow the match instead of the offset-adjusted match. This is because of the [current docs for `incsearch`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/71ac4db335e00b03b27d2c4aa5ab90c083a3a3e7/runtime/doc/options.txt#L3658-L3659\n), which say: “While typing a search command, show where the pattern, as it was typed so far, matches. The matched string is highlighted.” `c_CTRL-G` / `c_CTRL-T` are also documented in terms of moving to the next/prev “match”. Open to making this in a follow-up PR.",
